==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quilled
<hw>Quilled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Furnished with quills;
also, shaped like quills.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A sharp-<xex>quilled</xex>
porcupine.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Quilled suture</b></col> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>, <cd>a
variety of stitch in which the threads after being passed deeply through
the edges of a wound are secured about two quills or bodies of similar
shape, in order to produce a suitable degree of pressure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quillet</ent>⟦br⟧
